10 AS INTRODUCED
11 An Act relating to state development; creating the
Oklahoma Gas, Artificial Intelligence, and Space
12 Research Hub (GAS Hub); establishing the GAS Hub as
the State's central coordinating entity for
13 recruitment, development, and hosting of a National
Laboratory; clarifying that the GAS Hub shall
14 function as a state-federal partnership platform;
providing the purposes of the GAS Hub; directing the
15 Oklahoma Department of Commerce in coordination with
other state agencies to administer the GAS Hub;
16 authorizing the GAS Hub to enter public-private
partnerships for certain purposes; directing the GAS
17 Hub to prepare and maintain formal strategies;
directing the GAS Hub to submit an annual report;
18 establishing the Oklahoma National Laboratory
Development Program; directing the GAS Hub to
19 administer the program; granting the Oklahoma
Department of Commerce rulemaking authority;
20 providing for codification; and providing an
effective date.
21
22
23
24 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
HB3176 HFLR Page 1
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 5003.20 of Title 74, unless
3 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 There is hereby created the Oklahoma Gas, Artificial
5 Intelligence, and Space Research Hub (GAS Hub) to serve as the State
6 of Oklahoma's central coordinating entity for the recruitment,
7 development, and hosting of a United States National Laboratory.
8 The GAS Hub shall function as a state-federal partnership platform
9 to attract, secure, and support federal laboratory designation,
10 funding, and operations.
11 SECTION 2. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
12 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 5003.20a of Title 74, unless
13 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
14 A. The purposes of the Oklahoma Gas, Artificial Intelligence,
15 and Space Research Hub (GAS Hub) are to:
16 1. Position Oklahoma as a leading national center for:
17 a. advanced oil and gas research,
18 b. artificial intelligence and high-performance
19 computing, and
20 c. aerospace, space launch systems, and orbital
21 technologies;
22 2. Prepare and maintain federal-ready laboratory sites;
23 3. Coordinate workforce pipelines;
24 4. Aggregate state incentives and infrastructure; and
HB3176 HFLR Page 2
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 5. Serve as the formal applicant and liaison to the U.S.
2 Department of Energy, the National Aeronautics and Space
3 Administration, Department of War, and other federal agencies.
4 B. The GAS Hub shall be administered by the Oklahoma Department
5 of Commerce, and shall provide necessary staffing for the GAS Hub,
6 in coordination with:
7 1. The Oklahoma Corporation Commission;
8 2. The Oklahoma Space Industry Development Authority (OSIDA);
9 3. The State Regents for Higher Education;
10 4. The Oklahoma Department of Transportation; and
11 5. The Office of Management and Enterprise Services.
12 C. The GAS Hub may enter into public-private partnerships to:
13 1. Develop research parks;
14 2. Construct laboratory campuses;
15 3. Build high-performance computing facilities; and
16 4. Construct spaceport and test range infrastructure.
17 D. The GAS Hub shall prepare and maintain a formal strategy
18 for:
19 1. U.S. Department of Energy National Lab designation;
20 2. U.S. National Aeronautics and Space Administration center
21 designation;
22 3. U.S. Department of War research campus designation; and
23 4. Federally Funded Research and Development Center status.
24
HB3176 HFLR Page 3
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 E. The GAS Hub shall submit an annual report to the Governor,
2 President Pro Tempore of the Oklahoma Senate, and the Speaker of the
3 Oklahoma House of Representatives detailing:
4 1. Federal engagement;
5 2. Site readiness;
6 3. Funds expended;
7 4. Workforce pipeline development; and
8 5. Federal designation progress.
9 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
10 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 5003.20b of Title 74, unless
11 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
12 A. There is hereby created the Oklahoma National Laboratory
13 Development Program to:
14 1. Identify and certify federal-ready laboratory sites;
15 2. Pre-permit utility, water, rail, and highway access;
16 3. Aggregate state tax incentives;
17 4. Coordinate land acquisition and site assembly;
18 5. Maintain pre-approved environmental compliance documents;
19 and
20 6. Prepare formal federal applications.
21 B. This program shall be administered by the Oklahoma Gas,
22 Artificial Intelligence, and Space Research Hub in coordination with
23 other state agencies.
24
HB3176 HFLR Page 4
BOLD FACE denotes Committee Amendments.

1 SECTION 4. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
2 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 5003.20c of Title 74, unless
3 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
4 The Oklahoma Department of Commerce shall promulgate rules to
5 implement this act.
6 SECTION 5. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
7
